<!-- SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Bayside access without the premium price tag.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Wynnum West sits inland from Wynnum proper, occupying the affordable section of Brisbane's bayside corridor. It is a suburb that families have consistently targeted when Wynnum or Manly West prices have moved beyond their reach, and that demand pattern has given Wynnum West a steady growth story as the primary bayside suburbs appreciate. The combination of practical access to Wynnum's esplanade, schools and retail, larger block sizes than the waterfront suburbs, and a price point that allows buyers to own more home for their money, is what drives this market.
    </p>
