          What drives property values in Wynnum West?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Wynnum West property values are shaped by proximity to Wynnum's amenity corridor, block size, and access to the Wynnum-Manly rail line. Buyers who want bayside living but cannot reach Wynnum or Manly West on budget consistently target Wynnum West. Properties on quieter streets within easy reach of Wynnum's esplanade, school catchments and retail strip attract the strongest buyer interest.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Wynnum West?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Wynnum West homes typically sell within 30 to 50 days. Young families and buyers stepping up from Tingalpa make up the core buyer pool, and they arrive having compared Wynnum West directly against Wynnum and Manly West. Correctly priced properties that present the suburb's lifestyle and school access clearly attract motivated enquiry early in the campaign.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Wynnum West?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Wynnum West offers practical bayside living within easy reach of Wynnum's esplanade, cafes and waterfront parks, without the premium price attached to a Wynnum address. The suburb suits young families who want outdoor space, school catchment access and a short drive to the bay, at a price point that allows them to buy a larger home than they could afford in Wynnum proper.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Wynnum West a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Wynnum West remains a strong value proposition for families seeking bayside access at an accessible price point. As Wynnum itself has appreciated, buyers priced out of the primary market have moved to Wynnum West, bringing sustained demand that has supported consistent price growth. The suburb's fundamentals, including school catchments, motorway proximity and bayside access, are not going to change.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

